---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'January 1, 2025';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement | Skyhooked on Comfort"
  description="Skyhooked on Comfort's commitment to web accessibility for all users in the Phoenix Valley."
>
  <section class="bg-charcoal-50 py-16 border-b border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="font-display font-extrabold text-charcoal text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-2">Accessibility Statement</h1>
      <p class="font-body text-neutral-500 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="space-y-10 font-body text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">Our Commitment</h2>
          <p>Skyhooked on Comfort is committed to ensuring that our website is accessible to people with disabilities. We aim to meet or exceed the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards and continually work to improve the accessibility experience for all users.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">Measures We Take</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              'Semantic HTML structure with proper heading hierarchy',
              'Descriptive alt text on all meaningful images',
              'ARIA labels on interactive elements (navigation, accordions, forms)',
              'Sufficient color contrast ratios throughout the site (WCAG AA minimum)',
              'Keyboard navigability for all interactive elements',
              'Focus indicators visible on all focusable elements',
              'Form labels and error messaging for all form fields',
              'Responsive design functional at all zoom levels up to 400%',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-sky flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 12.75l6 6 9-13.5"/></svg>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">Known Limitations</h2>
          <p>While we strive for full accessibility, some areas of the site may not yet fully meet all WCAG 2.1 AA criteria. We are actively working to identify and address any gaps. Known limitations are tracked and prioritized for remediation in our development roadmap.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">Assistive Technologies</h2>
          <p>This site is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 ml-5 list-disc">
            <li>Screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver, TalkBack)</li>
            <li>Browser zoom and text resizing</li>
            <li>Keyboard-only navigation</li>
            <li>High contrast and inverted color display modes</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">Report an Accessibility Issue</h2>
          <p>If you encounter an accessibility barrier on our website, or if you need any content in an alternative format, please contact us. We take these reports seriously and will work to provide a solution or alternative access.</p>
          <div class="bg-charcoal-50 rounded-xl p-5 mt-4 border border-neutral-200">
            <p class="font-display font-semibold text-charcoal mb-2">Contact us about accessibility</p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:4801234567" class="text-sky hover:underline">(480) 123-4567</a></p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-neutral-500">We respond to accessibility reports within 2 business days.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">Formal Complaints</h2>
          <p>If you are not satisfied with our response to an accessibility complaint, you may contact the U.S. Department of Justice (DOJ) Civil Rights Division regarding ADA website accessibility requirements, or the Arizona Center for Disability Law for state-level guidance.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
